    "sizes": [
      14.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      71.71,
      312.34,
      453.04,
      410.37
    ],
    "text": "An information source is anything that might inform a person about something or provide knowledge of it. Information can come from different sources such as people, television or radio, newspapers, books, journals and magazines, encyclopedias, and web pages. Different types of questions require different sources of information. The type of information you need will change depending on the question you are trying to answer.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0,
      35.63079833984375
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      72.32,
      438.32,
      444.25,
      467.97
    ],
    "text": "Study the following examples of common sources of information and do the activities that follow.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      232.53,
      535.92,
      453.34,
      609.88
    ],
    "text": "A. These are collections of articles and pictures about various topics of popular interest and current events. Usually these articles are written by journalists or scholars.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      78.0,
      627.64,
      446.13,
      652.76
    ],
    "text": "52For free distribution",
